  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use these functions to create a new texture. While doing so, you should be aware of the memory implications of texture memory, and the other ways to get textures other than "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKTexture"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " initializers. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Memory Considerations",
          "anchor": "3020494"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When creating textures you should be aware of the memory consumed as a result of their file size dimensions. Often, the memory available to prepared textures is limited by hardware because textures are loaded in VRAM. Consider the following tips:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Access a texture only when needed and dispose of it when you are done. This frees up memory for other parts of the app."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Avoid loading too many textures in a single pass through the rendering loop. The process of decoding an image from disk is an expensive one and can therefore cause a few frames to be skipped. To avoid performance hiccups, preload textures ahead of time, such as when the scene is loaded."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If you frequently use that same textures together (for example, all the grass tiles any time grass is displayed in a scene) then you should consider bundling them into an "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktextureatlas"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to increase loading and runtime peformance. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Ways to Access Textures",
          "anchor": "3020493"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In addition to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktexture/texture_initializers"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKTexture"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the following other classes vend textures, too: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Access a texture by its original filename within a SpriteKit texture atlas folder using"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": " SKTextureAtlas"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "'s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sktextureatlas/1427375-texturenamed"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Create a texture by rendering an existing node in the tree, including its children, using "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "SKView"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "'s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skview/1520114-texturefromnode"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
